 data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hvm1665702877927.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvm1665702877927.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hvm1665702877927.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hvm1665702877927\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Language-Specific Applications\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__language_specific_applications_94941\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In a language specific Uniface, you can develop an application entirely in that language.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__p_d29129e1_d29130e1_d29131e1\">The Uniface IDE has an English user interface, even if you installed Uniface with a non-English character set. However, you can enter the non-English characters in labels, menu items, and so on to develop an application completely in that language.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__fig_d29135e1_d29136e1_d29137e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Simplified Chinese Application in Development (Uniface 9)</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Graphical content\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/development_in_simplified_chinese.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__fig_d29141e1_d29142e1_d29143e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Deployed Simplified Chinese Application</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Graphical content\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/deployment_in_simplified_chinese.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__p_d29147e1_d29148e1_d29149e1\">In a Uniface version installed with a specific character set, there are some restrictions on where the characters can be used.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__p_d29150e1_d29151e1_d29152e1\">In general, text that is visible to the user of your application can be in the specific language, for example in labels, menu items, ValRep lists, and so on.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hvm1665702877927__p_d29153e1_d29154e1_d29155e1\">Most object names can only use ASCII characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dpa1665702875291.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dpa1665702875291.html\" title=\"Although Uniface supports Unicode and the installable character sets, there are restrictions in using them.\">Restrictions on Use of Unicode and Installable Character Sets</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528390\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528390\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Language-Specific Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Language-Specific Applications In a language specific Uniface, you can develop an application entirely in that language. The Uniface IDE has an English user interface, even if you installed Uniface with a non-English character set. However, you can enter the non-English characters in labels, menu items, and so on to develop an application completely in that language. Figure 1. Simplified Chinese Application in Development (Uniface 9) Figure 2. Deployed Simplified Chinese Application In a Uniface version installed with a specific character set, there are some restrictions on where the characters can be used. In general, text that is visible to the user of your application can be in the specific language, for example in labels, menu items, ValRep lists, and so on. Most object names can only use ASCII characters. For more information, see Restrictions on Use of Unicode and Installable Character Sets . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}